                        <p>These and other considerations are discussed in a joint strategy discussion and lead to an investment strategy that is optimally tailored to you and your needs.</p>
                        <h3>High level of discipline</h3>
                        <p>Perhaps the most decisive factor for successful investment is discipline. The consistent implementation and monitoring of the defined investment strategy includes the continuous expansion of your portfolio and the allocation of investments to different asset classes. This avoids unnecessary investment risks such as emotional decisions, too much weighting of individual investment products, sectors and regions, or falling below a certain minimum credit rating of fixed-interest securities, which can have a negative impact on portfolio development.</p>
