                    <div id="monetization">
                        <div class="section-title">
                            <h2 class="display-4">Monetization<span>.</span></h2>
                        </div>
                        <p>Through existing credit relationships we are able to accommodate bank obligations such as bank guarantees (BG) and standby letter of credit (SBLC) for credit line and monetization facilities.</p>
                        <p>Bank instruments such as Documentary Letters of Credit (DLC) and Guarantees are frequently used but seldom properly understood. While these instruments are utilized in conventional trading on a day to day basis, they can also be employed in complex financial structures designed to maximize financial positions and bespoke to each individual requirement.</p>
                        <p>Commonly, Documentary Letters of Credit (DLC) are used for payment of shipped goods. Often referred to as DLCs or LCs, they serve to guarantee payment to one party upon the fulfilment of certain conditions, usually based around receiving specific goods. Wording and layout of a DLC is bespoke to the parties.</p>
                        <p>Bank Guarantees (BG) are used for guaranteeing payments in a number of given circumstances. Often referred to as BGs, they are worded specifically for the purpose and specifically written to the stated parties thereto. The use of BGs are becoming increasingly common, for example in lieu of deposit payments. Applicants may opt to issue a BG instead of parting with a cash deposit. They can also be used in intelligent financial structures. Standby Letters of Credit (SBLCs) are used in the USA in lieu of bank guarantees (BGs) and work in a similar fashion.</p>
                        <p>Through our international relationships, we are able to monetize your assets using many unique processes, customizable tools and instruments at our disposal. These unique tools will be tailored to unlock your financial potential in ways that banking institutions are unable to provide.</p>
                        <p>If you have dormant or stagnant assets like Fine Arts, Antiques, Real Estate, Tenders, Contracts, Tangible Assets e.t.c, our experienced experts can help you utilize and maximize those resources to your best advantage that may mean raising capital against them in hard cash or for trade indemnities and other types of guarantee requirements.</p>
                    </div>
