                    <div id="leasing-collateral">
                        <div class="section-title">
                            <h2 class="display-4">Leasing /<span>Collateral Transfer.</span></h2>
                        </div>
                        <p>For young companies or companies experiencing tough financial times, it is not always easy to convince your bankers to grant finance and loans when they are needed the most. It is common to find highly geared companies in times of recession and often companies have borrowed to the hilt of their assets. Some young companies may not have any borrowings at all; not because they are financially independent, but for the simple reason that banks and lenders will not grant any credit to them.</p>
                        <p>Bankers and lenders alike will demand security for any loan or investment. If the company has already used available equity or doesn’t have access to strong security, the options of borrowing are dramatically reduced.</p>
                        <p>Shareholders can of course be approached to raise further capital and the options of bond offerings and private placements may also be made. However, these avenues are not always the best course of action or the most economical. They can be long, drawn-out processes and the company may not have time or money to launch such complex financial actions.</p>
                        <p>In these circumstances, it may simply be preferable to import or lease collateral assets to offer as security for conventional borrowings.</p>
                        <p>Through Collateral Management and Security Leasing programmes, DFC has experience in providing collateral and security to potential borrowers on a short term to medium term leases that the borrowers can use to secure further bank borrowings with conventional bankers or from lending institutions arranged through our partnership by providing financial Guarantees or third party corporate Guarantees from multi-national conglomerates working closely with us, making it easier for potential borrowers to obtain bank borrowings and attract further investments thus growth.</p>
                        <p>Financial Guarantees, Third Party Guarantees and Collateral Leasing can be prove an effective solution to increase borrowings or for financing temporary, short term gaps and can be efficiently used as bridging finance.</p>
                        <p>From Security Lending to Collateral Transfer, DFC is positioned to advise the best and most suited programme for your needs, offering specific solutions and providing all-in collateral lending packages designed to suit your business requirements.</p>
                    </div>
